<br>
and where's the fun in that ?<br>
Let's, see. At first mages were &quot;ok you have an awesome pet, but you can't do hack in groups, hope you like to solo&quot;, then &quot;raiding is fun heh ? well not for you, since you can't land a single nuke on any mob and you can't use your pet since we don't know how to code pathing&quot;, then &quot;ok, you can raid now, sick pet on mob, look at a wall and click the same spell over and over, and pretend you like it&quot;.<br>
<br>
Call me bitter, but i can't recall the last time i had fun on a raid being a mage. Sure, pretty much all SoL raids can't be done without us now, but i'm still looking for the &quot;fun factor&quot; in the newly hyped Mod Rodding Frenzy.<br>
<br>
I picked mage to be a damaging class with pets and cool summons. Thx VI for turning my class into a 7/11.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, AC2 looks really cool.<br>
